theorem Topology.interior_union_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior A ∪ interior B ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) := by
  intro x hx
  cases hx with
  | inl hxA =>
      -- `A` is contained in `A ∪ B`, so the same holds for their interiors.
      have h_sub : interior A ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) :=
        interior_mono (by
          intro y hy
          exact Or.inl (interior_subset hy))
      exact h_sub hxA
  | inr hxB =>
      -- Symmetric argument for `B`.
      have h_sub : interior B ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) :=
        interior_mono (by
          intro y hy
          exact Or.inr (interior_subset hy))
      exact h_sub hxB
